Who else has tried to do a photoshoot with a toddler? It ain’t for the weak! Here are some tips to make it easier:

➡️Get a photographer that is patient & great with kids! It’s a plus if they have shot with kids before!
➡️Schedule photoshoot around nap/bed times! Mornings always worked the best for us
➡️Snacks! Snacks! Snacks! (My daughter had marshmallows & goldfish throughout this entire shoot 😅) 
➡️ Bonus tip: hire a stylist 👀 We’ve used @kiarralooks for all of our family/mommy & daughter photoshoots! Because half of the stress is figuring out what to wear & wanting to look our best during these special moments! (Mommy & daughter dresses designed by the talented @parisjodesigns ❤️‍🔥)

#photoshoot #mommydaughter #family #familyphotography #toddlermom #toddlerfashion #fashion #highfashion #highfashionphotography #instagramvsreality

Tips for your next photoshoot👇
•
•
•
1. Make sure to discuss concept of photoshoot with photographer & creative team so that everyone is on the same page! Including what items, if any, you’re responsible to bring to the photoshoot! 

2. Movement! Make sure to keep moving as the camera is clicking 📸! Small fluid movements are best while keeping focus on camera even as the photographer is giving direction (Trust me, it can turn into an amazing shot!)

3. Grab some behind the scenes shots/videos! Everything is content but make sure it is not in the way of where the photographer needs to move! (Also a great way to improve on your posing by watching yourself!)

4. Music! If you’re feeling nervous or a little stiff while posing, play some music to loosen up! Photoshoots should be fun so have fun with it!!

5. Save some inspo shots to your phone that you can quickly review before & during the photoshoot! This is great when you are wanting to try new poses & it can keep you from repeating the same poses! 

Practice makes perfect, so go out there and have fun while capturing some amazing shots!!!
